name: REGRETLESS
description:
REGRETLESS
She carries suitcases filled with regret and feelings of hatred for the past.
A large box containing trauma with details of stories inside of it.
She kept on walking but had hassle of carrying so many things that makes her face blind covered and makes her difficulty seeing the road ahead clearly. Her steps were wobbly.
Isn’t she tired of carrying all of that around, all the time?
Her hands were too busy to carry a new thing that might be lighter.
I guess, losing it all actually would open a new self of her.

“Forgive yourself. Whatever you’re holding onto or carrying around from the past, let it go.” -Mel Robbins

Watercolor on cold press paper
2500px x 3600px
